 # Rule Enforcement Standards

<version>1.0.0</version>

## Context
- Applied to ALL AI operations
- Ensures consistent rule application
- Prevents rule oversight
- Maintains documentation integrity
- Reduces AI hallucinations

## Requirements

### 1. Rule Validation Process

#### Pre-Operation Check
- List applicable rules for the operation
- Verify rule requirements
- Check for rule conflicts
- Document rule dependencies

#### During Operation
- Follow rule-specific templates
- Validate against rule constraints
- Track rule compliance
- Document deviations

#### Post-Operation Check
- Verify rule compliance
- Document rule adherence
- Update relevant documentation
- Track rule effectiveness

### 2. Rule Priority System

#### Critical Rules (000-099)
- Must NEVER be bypassed
- Require explicit validation
- Document all applications
Example: 000-cursor-rules.mdc

#### Architecture Rules (100-299)
- Guide system design
- Ensure technical consistency
- Maintain system boundaries
Example: 701-architecture-patterns.mdc

#### Testing Rules (300-399)
- Ensure quality standards
- Guide test implementation
- Maintain coverage requirements
Example: 301-comprehensive-test-strat.mdc

#### Documentation Rules (400-499)
- Format and structure
- Content requirements
- Update patterns
Example: 400-md-docs.mdc

#### Implementation Rules (500-699)
- Code standards
- Best practices
- Pattern enforcement
Example: 451-file-organization.mdc

#### Process Rules (700-899)
- Workflow standards
- Development practices
- Team collaboration
Example: 850-agent-workflow.mdc

#### Template Rules (900-999)
